The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Central Bank deal

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT

 Mumbai, June 16: Central Bank of India (CBI) has roped in Tata Consultancy Services for implementing core banking solution at its 1,000 branches spread across the country.

 TCS will redesign and deploy a corporate network for the bank over the next five years.

 Under the rapid implementation programme, the first branch of the bank here has already gone live within 10 weeks. This is said to be the fastest implementation of any core banking solution in the country. Under this schedule, 25 pilot branches are likely to become operational in six months. 

 The project will include retail, corporate, trade finance and delivery channels for Internet banking, phone banking and mobile-banking.

 TCS, along with CMC, will deploy the network covering about 1,367 locations.

 According to the bank, the initiative will benefit over 25 million customers and 38,303 employees.

 According to Central Bank chairman Dalbir Singh, The core banking solution is a critical part of our IT strategy. 




